The paper deals with problems related to discrete partitioning and geometric sampling, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of subspace designs and error-correcting codes in the paper suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The study of query complexity and the use of probabilistic methods suggest a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of combinatorial designs and partitions suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
